pullsbody:
Fixes #282


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_

pulltitle: Add filter to vote admin that uses a select box for display.
pullsbody:
Admin filters [have a template property](https://github.com/django/django/blob/1.4.5/django/contrib/admin/filters.py#L21) that the [admin change list template](https://github.com/django/django/blob/1.4.5/django/contrib/admin/templates/admin/change_list.html#L81) uses to [lookup and render](https://github.com/django/django/blob/1.4.5/django/contrib/admin/templatetags/admin_list.py#L365) the list of filter options. [The default filter template](https://github.com/django/django/blob/1.4.5/django/contrib/admin/templates/admin/filter.html) uses an unordered list of links to display the available filter options, but a select box is better for things like related fields that may have a TON of choices.

This PR adds a filter that uses a select box and is subsequently used to filter votes by the video they are assigned to in the admin interface.

pullsbody:
Encompasses @craigcook's work from #235 and the work needed to make it work with the autocomplete code from #242.

A few notes:
- To save on time I had to cut a few corners; the sort dropdown is a separate form and has copies of the query, field, and region inputs. A better solution would be to create a separate form that only does sorting or handle it in the view somewhere.
- I removed the anchor tags from the autocomplete since I already had JS code to handle clicking the list elements. In an ideal world, the JavaScript would generate a link and assign the href of the anchors to keep the dropdown semantic, but time constraints. Boo!
- There's a few strings I'm not so sure about, such as the search submit button, but since part of this week is having the stakeholders look over the site and suggest changes, we can bring them up then.

pull_commit_message:
Bug 886500: Add autocomplete dropdown.

Adds a JS-powered widget to the search page that shows suggested
completions for a user's search term. It's not super-smart; in the
background it performs the search and returns the first result found,
which isn't weighted by a score or anything, so it's mostly a shot in
the dark. But it's not terrible if you're searching for a semi-unique
string; the primary use-case here is people searching for videos by
their friends.

The design of the frontend bits are in one of craigcook's pull
requests, and I'll be integrating it later. The JavaScript is
functionally complete, although it will be modified to fit whatever
frontend craigcook came up with.

I decided to try a different approach to the JavaScript bits by
separating the widget logic with the DOM-handling code. It's a little
verbose in this case, but I'm actually quite happy with the result.

pullsbody:
Adds a basic search feature to the video listing page.

We expect a maximum of around 400 submissions to Flicks by the time the contest is over, and we don't need the search to be super-powerful or super-accurate, so we opted to just use a simple contains filter to make the search work. I tested on a local database with around 40,000 entries and a multi-term search took about 20 milliseconds, so there's little concern over the performance of the search.

pullsbody:

if it isn't, activates some simple form validation. The only attribute

pulltitle: Fix bug 849913: Fix unicode issues with video titles and descriptions.
pullsbody:
Vimeo can't accept encoded UTF-8 in API requests, but it can accept
HTML-entity-encoded text, so we encode titles and descriptions as ASCII
and convert any unicode characters to HTML/XML entities.

Other fixes:
- Remove django-csp from the app list as the migrations for csp break my
  local MySQL database and we aren't using reporting anyway.
- Add /video/upload/error/ URL that accidentally got removed; the upload
  error code in the JS uses it.
pull_commit_message:
Fix bug 849913: Fix unicode issues with video titles and descriptions.

Vimeo can't accept encoded UTF-8 in API requests, but it can accept
HTML-entity-encoded text, so we encode titles and descriptions as ASCII
and convert any unicode characters to HTML/XML entities.

Other fixes:
- Remove django-csp from the app list as the migrations for csp break my
  local MySQL database and we aren't using reporting anyway.
- Add /video/upload/error/ URL that accidentally got removed; the upload
  error code in the JS uses it.

pull_commit_message:
Bug 840716: Download thumbnail image instead of storing URLs.

- Adds an admin command to download thumbnails for existing videos.
- Alters the approval processing to happen synchronously on save instead
  of asynchronously via celery to help lower the risk of making a video
  public before it is fully processed.
- Move approval email outside of process_approval to avoid emailing the
  user before the video changes have completed and been saved 
  successfully.
- Bug 840717: Only show pagination if there is more than one page of
  results.
- send_approval_email now uses the default locale if the user doesn't
  have a locale or profile.
- Improve test patching to avoid contacting outside services during
  tests.

pulltitle: Temporarily redirect invalid locales to the homepage.
pullsbody:
Funfactory's LocaleURLMiddleware will tack en-US onto any URL without an
active locale, such as /fr -> /en-US/fr/. This causes 404s when it tries
to match on the url /fr.

This is a temporary fix that redirects any path that starts with a
locale-like string to the homepage. This should catch any redirects with
locales in the path and just push users towards the homepage. We'll 
remove this once the locales we want are back in.
pull_commit_message:
Temporarily redirect invalid locales to the homepage.

Funfactory's LocaleURLMiddleware will tack en-US onto any URL without an
active locale, such as /fr -> /en-US/fr/. This causes 404s when it tries
to match on the url /fr.

This is a temporary fix that redirects any path that starts with a
locale-like string to the homepage. This should catch any redirects with
locales in the path and just push users towards the homepage. We'll 
remove this once the locales we want are back in.

pulltitle: Update django-browserid and replace submit button when logged out.
pullsbody:
If a user is logged out and clicks the submit button, the site currently
shows them a page in the frame that auto-triggers Persona login, causing
a popup warning. This patch fixes this by instead replacing the submit
button with a login button when the user isn't logged in, and uses an 
anchor in the URL to trigger the submission modal after login is 
finished.
pull_commit_message:
Update django-browserid and replace submit button when logged out.

If a user is logged out and clicks the submit button, the site currently
shows them a page in the frame that auto-triggers Persona login, causing
a popup warning. This patch fixes this by instead replacing the submit
button with a login button when the user isn't logged in, and uses an 
anchor in the URL to trigger the submission modal after login is 
finished.

Sorry for the giant PR, most of it is updating requests and adding requests-oauthlib to vendor-local.
- Makes profile creation view actually completable.
- Adds video upload flow. The final frontend for this will be different, it's mostly repurposed from my prototype code and is reasonably close.
- Moves old videos to Video2012 model and makes a new Video2013 model for this year's contest, with an alias so that most code just uses Video. When 2014 rolls around we'll add an archive that uses the 2013 model and add a new model for 2014 (which will probably have different metadata requirements and thus a different table) and update the alias.

pulltitle: Fix for quotes in video title attributes
pullsbody:
Enclosing the attribute value in single quotes allows double quotes in the value. This is just a short term hack to avoid string changes. We can get away with this because none of the video titles in question contain an apostrophe.

In the next revision we should instead encode those quotes as entities, or else solve the problems with verbatim and unicode characters.
pull_commit_message:
Fix title quotation marks for videos

Enclosing the attribute value in single quotes allows double quotes in the value. This is just a short term hack to avoid string changes. We can get away with this because none of the video titles in question contain an apostrophe.

pull_commit_message:
Add noop migration to fix created field issues.

Because there are two 0006 migrations, south keeps detecting the
created field as new and tries to add it to auto-generated migrations.
By adding a noop with the created field in the model definition,
we can force south to stop auto-detected created as new.

pullsbody:
Adds the ability to search via a MyISAM search table with a FULLTEXT index over the title column.

Also includes an unrelated setting that explicitly sets where the extract command should look for files to parse.
pull_commit_message: Specify which files to extract strings from.

pullsbody:
Adds the ability to search via a MyISAM search table with a FULLTEXT index over the title column.

Also includes an unrelated setting that explicitly sets where the extract command should look for files to parse.
pull_commit_message:
Add ability to search for video titles.

Adds a new model VideoSearchEntry, and uses MyISAM for the table
storage so that we can use a FULLTEXT index for searching video
titles, but retain the goodness of InnoDB on the rest of our
tables. Includes a cron management command to update the search
table.

pullsbody:
Adds video 'upload' form to the app. Lacking severly in the 'hooking up to the UI' part, though; you'll have to manually enter the URLs to access the upload form. Also adds a video embed into the video details page.

Note that local video upload won't work without using a service like localtunnel and changing your SITE_URL to match; this is because vid.ly requires a notification URL to let you know when the video is done converting, and they can't access localhost. :)

Also includes a bunch of test helpers to make our life easier.
